reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This sweater is high quality. It is thin and the pattern is such that you really need to wear an underpinning - but it’s beautiful and lightweight. Can’t wait to wear it in the spring. The blue color is lovely

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Slimming design! Love it!
reviews.reviewText: This Grace Karin sweater checks all the boxes for me! I’m a curvy girl. Sweaters in particular can make my figure look a little balloon-ish. Never my favorite look so…this one’s a hit!It has a collar, so you can easily dress the sweater up or down. it has a slimming, vertical line design woven in the fabric.I like to layer, and this sweater would be good for layering. The fabric is thin. In fact, it has a little bit of sheerness to it. I’m OK with a little sheerness because I won’t get overheated wearing the sweater. I also think it makes it lay on my figure in a more flattering way.Everything is very well done. The knitting of the fabric, the stitching & seams. Even the sizing. Grace Karin has become my go to brand! When I order something from this brand, I’m not disappointed!I absolutely love it! I have it in two colors now. I would highly recommend it. I hope it looks just as great on you!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Falling apart so sad
reviews.reviewText: Really like the fit and the rusty orange color was exactly what I wanted. The photo with darker orange is more true to actual color. So sad that after only two washes and laying it flat to dry the seams are coming apart. Too late to return so I will try to repair it. Maybe it’s a one off but very disappointed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This sweater is better than expected. It is gorgeous and I can’t wait to wear it. It has a chemical smell, so it needs to air out first. Haven’t washed it yet but, I may just toss it in the dryer for 10 minutes and then air dry naturally. Ordering more colors soon.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is probably going to be my number one shirt for the rest of this winter. Warm, cozy, comfortable, and stylish. Absolutely must have in your closet

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 12, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Really disappointed with this long sleeve shirt. Lifted it up in the air to look at and noticed how completely sheer it was. Not what I was interested in wearing especially when it’s freezing outside. I don’t own a matching undershirt and wouldn’t buy one just for this tissue paper thin, flimsy, cheap looking shirt. The price is entirely too high for something so thin and sheer.
